
Overview of verb linger

The verb linger has 5 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (3) linger -- (remain present although waning or gradually dying; "Her perfume lingered on")
2. (2) loiter, lounge, footle, lollygag, loaf, lallygag, hang around, mess about, tarry, linger, lurk, mill about, mill around -- (be about; "The high school students like to loiter in the Central Square"; "Who is this man that is hanging around the department?")
3. (2) tarry, linger -- (leave slowly and hesitantly)
4. (1) linger, dawdle -- (take one's time; proceed slowly)
5. hover, linger -- (move to and fro; "The shy student lingered in the corner")
